Whoever he is, he has terrified dozens of witnesses, who have never been the same afterwards. The brutal history of Cornwall Jail, Ottawa’s most notorious prison, lives on as ghostly apparitions of tortured inmates terrorize modern visitors. In its heyday it was home to vicious criminals, and sadistic guards. Hangings, whippings and torture were daily affairs and spirits from that era still linger on in the maze of cell blocks and corridors. Many male criminals were hanged at the Northwest Mounted Police outpost known as Fort Saskatchewan, but only one woman. Florence Lassandro was dubbed the Mob Princess, and her spirit is one of many seen on the grounds and in the preserved buildings of this historic site. Journey through several of the world's most haunted prisons and experience real portals to hell on earth.

programme.title: Wild Shots
programme.desc: In this episode of Wildshots, host Tim Harmsen heads to Sig Sauer for an exclusive look inside one of America’s most advanced firearms manufacturing facilities. With a motto of “Every day you wake up and get a little better,” Sig Sauer lives up to its words—producing over 5,000 firearms a day with cutting-edge robotics and precision automation. After a full factory tour, Tim hits Sig’s state-of-the-art testing range to get hands-on with the legendary XM250 machine gun, pushing the limits of modern firepower. Then it’s time for some pure shooting mastery as Tim meets up with friend and firearms influencer 22Plinkster. Known for his unbelievable accuracy and showmanship, 22Plinkster ups the ante—splitting playing cards with a .22 bullet, upside down, and even splitting a single bullet mid-flight to hit two separate targets at once. Finally, the episode caps off with a nod to Hollywood as Tim checks out the Genesis Arms machinery seen in John Wick, blending cinematic cool with real-world firepower.

programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: With the mission complete, the contestants think the season is winding down—but HQ has other plans. Their once-fabricated cover story becomes reality, pulling them into a pulse-pounding new challenge designed to test strength, coordination, and mastery of weaponry. This hybrid competition pushes every skill to the limit, weeding out all but the most well-rounded tactical athletes. Along the way, the legendary Don Mann shares his own backstory, giving rare insight into the life and mindset of the man behind the mission. When the dust settles, only one competitor will rise above the rest—earning the title of the season’s most complete warrior.

programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: Ken Shamrock’s Iron Man competition comes to a head as two contestants battle it out for the number one spot. Every strike, every takedown matters—because only one can walk away crowned the victor. But there’s no time to celebrate. It’s mission day. After a quick live-fire break, the team receives critical intel from the ISR daylight crew. The risk spikes as night falls and the mission is suddenly altered, forcing the contestants to adapt on the fly. With Red Cat providing coordination from above, the squad is redeployed under new marching orders and even higher stakes. A partially compromised team makes survival uncertain, but when the moment of truth arrives, the team leader takes decisive action—leading a direct breach on the target. One bold decision shifts the course of the mission entirely, and its success now hangs by a thread.

programme.title: The Big Reveal
programme.desc: Sheriff Mark Lamb (Surviving Mann) and UFC Hall of Famer Ken Shamrock (Surviving Mann) uncover a breakthrough changing how we live in a world full of invisible forces. Join them as Aires Tech reveals the science behind a revolutionary technology built to protect the human body from electromagnetic stress—empowering performance in a wired world.

programme.title: Crown Prince of Christmas
programme.desc: Madison, an aspiring musician, jokingly tells her overbearing family that she is dating the prince of a small European nation. Little does Madison know that Sebastian happens to be hiding a royal secret.

programme.title: Operation Orozco: Cartel Laundry
programme.desc: FBI agent Ed Guillen goes undercover as a banker to cozy up with a Columbian cartel member and help launder his dirty cash. programme.title: Operation Lockdown: Imprisoned Cop Killer
programme.desc: FBI agent Steve Salmieri takes on the alias of a mob hitman to go inside a prison to get evidence against a cop killer incarcerated on another charge. Salmieri rebuffs the cop killer's attempts at friendship, to convince him he's not someone to mess with. While wired for sound, Salmieri gets dozens of conversations on tape against the perp, but will it be enough to convict him of the murder of a police officer?

programme.title: Operation Komex: Selling Sarin
programme.desc: US Customs agent Rick Kennan masquerades as a weapons dealer to get inside a Korean arms operation that's soliciting military secrets and weapons. The case explodes when Kennan learns the arms dealer is looking to purchase sarin gas for a Middle East nation. The dealer will do anything for a price. But can Kennan move fast enough to intercept the 500 quarter-ton sarin bombs before they are delivered into the wrong hands?

programme.title: Operation Orozco: Cartel Laundry
programme.desc: FBI agent Ed Guillen goes undercover as a banker to cozy up with a Columbian cartel member and help launder his dirty cash. Guillen launders millions while taping incriminating conversations that will eventually convict the drug kingpin. In the end, Guillen uses his cunning to befriend the kingpin and get him to confess the extent of his illegal operation. The agent gains his trust and the dealer is sent to prison, forfeiting millions.

programme.title: Operation Lockdown: Imprisoned Cop Killer
programme.desc: FBI agent Steve Salmieri takes on the alias of a mob hitman to go inside a prison to get evidence against a cop killer incarcerated on another charge. Salmieri rebuffs the cop killer's attempts at friendship, to convince him he's not someone to mess with. While wired for sound, Salmieri gets dozens of conversations on tape against the perp, but will it be enough to convict him of the murder of a police officer?

programme.title: Operation Komex: Selling Sarin
programme.desc: US Customs agent Rick Kennan masquerades as a weapons dealer to get inside a Korean arms operation that's soliciting military secrets and weapons. The case explodes when Kennan learns the arms dealer is looking to purchase sarin gas for a Middle East nation. The dealer will do anything for a price. But can Kennan move fast enough to intercept the 500 quarter-ton sarin bombs before they are delivered into the wrong hands?

programme.title: Operation Orozco: Cartel Laundry
programme.desc: FBI agent Ed Guillen goes undercover as a banker to cozy up with a Columbian cartel member and help launder his dirty cash. Guillen launders millions while taping incriminating conversations that will eventually convict the drug kingpin. In the end, Guillen uses his cunning to befriend the kingpin and get him to confess the extent of his illegal operation. The agent gains his trust and the dealer is sent to prison, forfeiting millions.

programme.title: Operation Lockdown: Imprisoned Cop Killer
programme.desc: FBI agent Steve Salmieri takes on the alias of a mob hitman to go inside a prison to get evidence against a cop killer incarcerated on another charge. Salmieri rebuffs the cop killer's attempts at friendship, to convince him he's not someone to mess with. While wired for sound, Salmieri gets dozens of conversations on tape against the perp, but will it be enough to convict him of the murder of a police officer?

programme.title: Operation Komex: Selling Sarin
programme.desc: US Customs agent Rick Kennan masquerades as a weapons dealer to get inside a Korean arms operation that's soliciting military secrets and weapons. The case explodes when Kennan learns the arms dealer is looking to purchase sarin gas for a Middle East nation. The dealer will do anything for a price. But can Kennan move fast enough to intercept the 500 quarter-ton sarin bombs before they are delivered into the wrong hands?

programme.title: Operation Orozco: Cartel Laundry
programme.desc: FBI agent Ed Guillen goes undercover as a banker to cozy up with a Columbian cartel member and help launder his dirty cash. Guillen launders millions while taping incriminating conversations that will eventually convict the drug kingpin. In the end, Guillen uses his cunning to befriend the kingpin and get him to confess the extent of his illegal operation. The agent gains his trust and the dealer is sent to prison, forfeiting millions.

programme.title: Operation Lockdown: Imprisoned Cop Killer
programme.desc: FBI agent Steve Salmieri takes on the alias of a mob hitman to go inside a prison to get evidence against a cop killer incarcerated on another charge. Salmieri rebuffs the cop killer's attempts at friendship, to convince him he's not someone to mess with. While wired for sound, Salmieri gets dozens of conversations on tape against the perp, but will it be enough to convict him of the murder of a police officer?

programme.title: Operation Komex: Selling Sarin
programme.desc: US Customs agent Rick Kennan masquerades as a weapons dealer to get inside a Korean arms operation that's soliciting military secrets and weapons. The case explodes when Kennan learns the arms dealer is looking to purchase sarin gas for a Middle East nation. The dealer will do anything for a price. But can Kennan move fast enough to intercept the 500 quarter-ton sarin bombs before they are delivered into the wrong hands?

programme.title: Operation Orozco: Cartel Laundry
programme.desc: FBI agent Ed Guillen goes undercover as a banker to cozy up with a Columbian cartel member and help launder his dirty cash. Guillen launders millions while taping incriminating conversations that will eventually convict the drug kingpin. In the end, Guillen uses his cunning to befriend the kingpin and get him to confess the extent of his illegal operation. The agent gains his trust and the dealer is sent to prison, forfeiting millions.

programme.title: Operation Lockdown: Imprisoned Cop Killer
programme.desc: FBI agent Steve Salmieri takes on the alias of a mob hitman to go inside a prison to get evidence against a cop killer incarcerated on another charge. Salmieri rebuffs the cop killer's attempts at friendship, to convince him he's not someone to mess with. While wired for sound, Salmieri gets dozens of conversations on tape against the perp, but will it be enough to convict him of the murder of a police officer?

programme.title: Operation Komex: Selling Sarin
programme.desc: US Customs agent Rick Kennan masquerades as a weapons dealer to get inside a Korean arms operation that's soliciting military secrets and weapons. The case explodes when Kennan learns the arms dealer is looking to purchase sarin gas for a Middle East nation. The dealer will do anything for a price. But can Kennan move fast enough to intercept the 500 quarter-ton sarin bombs before they are delivered into the wrong hands?
